Create and sell your NFTs

1. Set up your wallet

Once you've set up your wallet of choice, connect it to OpenSeaby clicking the NFT Marketplacein the top right corner.

2. Create Your Collection

Click Create and set up your collection. Add social links, a description, profile & banner images, and set a secondary sales fee.

3. Add Your NFTs

Upload your work (image, video, audio, or 3D art), add a title and description, and customize your NFTs with properties, stats.

4. List Them For Sale

Choose between auctions, fixed-price listings, and declining-price listings. You choose how you want to sell your NFTs!

The Power of Digital Influencers: A Roadmap for Success

Here are some steps that can be taken to successfully sell one's latest NFT and/or promote future collections. Of course, it should be noted that for the success of NFT on a large scale and growing sales, a strong digital influencer marketing with complete works is needed and this is definitely justified and one and only effective way.

Community Creation

The goal of creating a community around Project NFT Art is to create meaningful relationships fueled by feedback, encouragement, and engagement. A dedicated community interacts with the refined content of the project, follows it on its long-term perspective journey, sees the value of the project's work, and looks forward to the project's future NFT ups and downs to success. You need to create an NFT community, then assess what the target audience wants, develop a good roadmap to guide the project, and then develop a good game plan. A truly legitimate goal is to encourage followers, keep them happy, constantly foster a supportive community to encourage them, and keep them engaged. Of course, with consistent effort, over time it's possible to build a dedicated online community of hundreds—if not thousands—of organic fans.

The power of social media is strategic:

Setting up and expanding your own social media channels is an important way to increase the community within the project, to improve the project's online presence, of course to expand the target audience and to spread the word about the existing NFT art collections and branding. In addition, it allows to better organize and analyze, segment the personal audience, and as a result, the target audience is defined. Growing success requires an active push for future sales on social media using both organic and paid methods to increase traffic and sales within the project for NFTs in the long term, while organic methods include sharing photos, videos and user-generated content, as well as a supportive community ( with followers) to engage, through comments and messages. Examples of paid methods are ads and sponsored posts.
